=begin
  Proof of concept for adding urchin shortcuts in mapdb.

  Currently:
    - links endpoints together, not every room that you can use URCHIN GUIDE from.
    - adds links and rooms to the local mapdb, but doesn't save them.
    - must be run once per town and per login to add them, unless you save your map on your own.
    - only uses urchins when go2 is running, so it won't interfere with child2, ego2, official2, step2, or other movement scripts
    
  Usage:
    ;use_urchins
      - checks URCHIN STATUS
      - updates UserVars.mapdb_use_urchins (boolean)
      - updates UserVars.mapdb_urchins_expire (expiration time as integer)
      - If you can use urchins,
        and you haven't already scanned the current town recently or that scan was complete, will scan it.
        - creates a fake room to handle shortcuts, if it doesn't exist.

    ;use_urchins rescan
      - rescan for debugging
      - If you can use urchins, scans the current town.
        - creates a fake room to handle shortcuts, if it doesn't exist.

  To reset your local mapdb:
      ;e Map.reload

          author: Xanlin (Xanlin#4407 on discord)
            game: GS
            tags: travel, mapdb, go2, urchin
        required: Lich >= 4.6.4
         version: 1.0.1
=end
UserVars.mapdb_use_urchins = true if UserVars.mapdb_use_urchins.nil?;
UserVars.mapdb_urchins_expire = 0 if UserVars.mapdb_urchins_expire.nil?;
UserVars.delete('urchins_enable') if UserVars.keys.include?('urchins_enable')
UserVars.delete('urchins_expires') if UserVars.keys.include?('urchins_expires')
UserVars.delete('urchins_towns') if UserVars.urchins_towns;
$urchins_towns   = {}    if $urchins_towns.nil?;
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
